# Architecture

Business logic lives only in `packages/core`. Everything else is a delivery mechanism around it.

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    core["packages/core<br/>domain + ports + services<br/>(pure Python)"]
    be["apps/backend<br/>FastAPI + SQLModel"]
    cli["apps/cli<br/>{{ cli_name }}"]
{%- if include_web_frontend %}
    fe["apps/frontend<br/>React + typed client"]
{%- endif %}
{%- if desktop_framework == 'pyside6' %}
    dt["apps/desktop-qt<br/>PySide6 shell"]
{%- elif desktop_framework != 'none' %}
    dt["apps/desktop<br/>{{ desktop_framework }} shell"]
{%- endif %}

    cli --> core
    be --> core
{%- if include_web_frontend %}
    fe -->|HTTP| be
{%- endif %}
{%- if desktop_framework == 'pyside6' %}
    dt -->|in-process services + events| core
{%- elif desktop_framework != 'none' %}
    dt -->|in-process bridge| be
{%- endif %}
```

| Layer | Responsibility |
| --- | --- |
| `packages/core` | Domain models, repository ports, services. No FastAPI, no DB, no HTTP. |
| `apps/backend` | FastAPI adapter; owns SQLModel persistence + Alembic migrations. |
| `apps/cli` | Typer CLI (`{{ cli_name }}`) — another adapter and the task runner. |
{%- if include_web_frontend %}
| `apps/frontend` | React web UI over a client generated from the OpenAPI schema. |
{%- endif %}
{%- if desktop_framework == 'pyside6' %}
| `apps/desktop-qt` | Native Qt widgets over the core, in-process; core events reach widgets via a Qt dispatcher. |
{%- elif desktop_framework != 'none' %}
| `apps/desktop` | Native window over the same UI; API calls dispatched in-process (no HTTP). |
{%- endif %}
| `packages/licensing` | Entitlement: dev stub, signed offline tokens, file/HTTP providers. |
| `packages/plugin-api`, `extensions/` | The plugin SDK and example plugins. |

To extend the app, prefer a **plugin** (see `extensions/`) over editing the core.
